ution, please proceed

Good afternoon Grant,

Thanks for your email below. My client does not accept that this scope incl=
udes all the necessary work to reinstate the fire damage at her house. Howe=
ver, in order to keep this claim moving towards resolution, please proceed =
to cost Tower=E2=80=99s scope of works as you suggest.

My client=E2=80=99s experts will review the scope and repair methodology an=
d we will revert. Due to the time of year, this will not be until late Janu=
ary. Some issues which we require expert input on include:

  1.  Checking the structural methodology
  2.  Building Consent Costs, including engineering
  3.  Any consideration of Heritage/Natural Character Overlay requirements =
specific to 23 Mays Street
  4.  Any assessment/provisional cost for water pipe damage (informed by th=
e fire service reporting likely damage)
  5.  Any assessment/provisional cost for gas lines and gas unit
  6.  Soot, PAH, VOC or other combustion testing for carbon
  7.  Potential for damage / contamination in wiring
  8.  Potential knock-on consequences for electrical in the rest of the hou=
se
  9.  Insulation removal/replacement in cavities
  10. Moisture mapping
  11. Mould assessment or treatment
  12. Potential corrosion from chlorides
We will let you know when this is completed.

Lance, we are waiting for your assessment of temporary accommodation costs.=
 We discussed whether an additional sum could be paid on the basis that the=
re was delay in commissioning testing. Raffaella is now out of pocket for t=
emporary accommodation so your response on this point would be appreciated.

Kind regards


