ont-size:1.0pt;color:white"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Good afternoon Grant,</span><span lang=
=3D"EN-NZ"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">&nbsp;</span><span lang=3D"EN-NZ"><o:p=
></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Thanks for your email below. My client=
 does not accept that this scope includes all the necessary work to reinsta=
te the fire damage at her house. However, in order
 to keep this claim moving towards resolution, please proceed to cost Tower=
=E2=80=99s scope of works as you suggest.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">My client=E2=80=99s experts will revie=
w the scope and repair methodology and we will revert. Due to the time of y=
ear, this will not be until late January. Some issues which
 we require expert input on include:</span><span lang=3D"EN-NZ"><o:p></o:p>=
</span></p>
